No greenwashing bulls**t here 

Here’s part 3 of this series of popular reels showcasing some of the very best small, sustainable fashion brands. There are so many incredible small makers out there that we need to shine a spotlight on and shout about so let’s get started with a summary of each:

@studio.spokes 
Tash is makes the dreamiest blouses and camis ever. These are made from vintage tea towels and after discussing what theme I was after she showed me lots of amazing options and provided the best bespoke design experience. All her pieces are SO flattering on and the workmanship and quality of each one is incredible. 

@melissamunrodesign 
The best denim shirt I’ve ever had, it’s been reworked in such a clever way from an old vintage Levi’s one, the detail on the sleeves and the cute neck tie make it really special, these were made as a collab with @pavement_store_london. There’s also some great dress shirts to choose from. 

@aftercare.apparel 
Dora embroiders old, preloved clothing and brings them to life with her fun tattoo inspired designs. I went for this plain Cos dress and it’s magic how it’s gone from plain and simple old dress to this fun themed cowboy mini, so clever and makes boring old clothes destined for landfill into fresh, fun ones full of personality. 

@laoisecareystudio 
I have loved this blouse ever since seeing it on @angelascanlon. After chatting about it with Irish brand founder Laoise she sold me this one before it was destined for a sample sale. It’s beautifully made and I love Laoise’s choices of fabric, her pieces are also currently available in a collection for @officialbrownthomas .

@ivy_thebrand 
I am so relieved I never have to search for t shirts again. Ivy does it so well and specialise in the perfect tee, there’s different styles and colours and each one I’ve tried is so spot on. The quality of them is far superior to any cheap, poor quality high street number and yes there’s matching kids ones ☺️ 

Trousers @_beyond_nine 

