No matter the dress code, there are some general guidelines to ensure your outfit is sustainable. Choose materials like organic cotton, linen, and silk – they’re much more eco-friendly than synthetics like polyester. Opt for pieces you can wear repeatedly rather than one-time wonders.

In my opinion renting is the clear winner. Why? Because when you rent, you’re not creating any new demand for clothing production. Plus, you’re not stuck with a piece of clothing that you may only wear once or twice. It’s a win-win!

